threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, EABI4 version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, with debug_info, not stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a sophisticated IoT botnet, likely a variant of Mirai or Gafgyt, designed for DDoS attacks and remote command execution. Key malicious behaviors include: 1) A comprehensive DDoS suite implemented in functions like attacks_udp, attacks_stomp, attacks_raknet, attacks_tfo, and attacks_gre. 2) Command-and-control (C2) capabilities via command_parse, which can spawn a reverse shell using /bin/sh. 3) Anti-competitive features in tcp_kill_port that scan /proc/net/tcp and /proc/pid/exe to identify and kill rival processes on specific ports. 4) Persistence/Single-instance locking by binding to port 45295 (0xb0ef). 5) Integrated SOCKS5 proxy support for anonymizing traffic or pivoting through the infected host. Relevant IOCs include the use of port 45295 for locking and the specific DDoS attack patterns registered in attack_init.
